description.en: Pantos is an open-source research project founded by the team behind Bitpanda and is being developed in collaboration with researchers at the Technical University of Vienna. The project aims to establish an open standard for truly decentralised cross-blockchain token transfers and blockchain interoperability. Over the course of the last few years, several working Proof of Concept solutions have been released, displaying our research results and highlighting the importance of blockchain agnostic solutions. While today's interoperability solutions are often designed in a (semi) centralised manner, Pantos aims to enable the transfer of tokens to other blockchains without the need for an intermediary blockchain, thus always preserving the security and integrity of the involved blockchains.
